If I misunderstood, then I certainly apologize.

Perhaps we&#39;d react differently if you participated here more often-- 
posting your own files and asking questions of researchers. For  
example, &quot;Hey, Ann--that file you just posted, I hear what you do,  
but is anything clipped out of it? I think I hear a track silenced,  
too. If so, why did you do that?&quot; Then I get to answer and explain  
why I did it that way, offer the raw clip, or whatever. It doesn&#39;t  
come off as a broad attack--just a friendly question. Even Bruce  
wouldn&#39;t rip out your living eyeballs for that. (Well... maybe he  
wouldn&#39;t, anyway. ;) )

I agree with your search for The Truth. I really do. That&#39;s why you  
see me get all rough-and-tumble over stuff like the Luminator when I  
think it is it lacking convincing evidence. But it&#39;s waaaaaay too  
early in &quot;boxology&quot; to try to make it perform as a pet circus animal.  
Hell, we&#39;ve been studying traditional EVP for 30 years and it still  
won&#39;t perform on cue for the scientists or anyone else. But if you  
just listen to what you get on your own and what all the others are  
getting, it becomes very clear indeed that a real phenomenon is  
occurring. Sure, some things we get that we think are paranormal may  
be just radio fragments, but one radio fragment does not negate all  
box communication. One tweaked clip is not indicative of a culture of  
researcher deceit. One &quot;I am Bazoozoo! Time to fry, foolish mortal!&quot;  
does not mean that the RS hacks are pathways to Satan&#39;s indoor  
plumbing. There are no easy answers yet--and there may never be any.  
And I&#39;m not sure we&#39;re at the stage yet where we have the right to  
demand The Truth or whether we would even see it if it was staring us  
in the face.

All right, enough joy in myself one-hand clapping.

LC is right that if you want to try to pursue this in the way you  
want to pursue it, then you need to find some people who share your  
mindset and go to it. I don&#39;t think you&#39;re going to find those people  
here, necessarily--at least among the old guard. We&#39;re the beatniks  
in black leather, smoking ciggies and reading bad poetry to the beat  
of bongos, HMO.

Ann

